{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place herbs in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl and place Varoma into position. Weigh in Brussels sprouts, cover with Varoma lid and steam <b>14-16 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, or until Brussels sprouts are tender. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside to keep warm. Discard water.","Place shallots in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add pancetta, butter and reserved chopped herbs then sauté <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add chestnuts, Marsala, maple syrup, salt and pepper then, without measuring cup, cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Transfer to bowl with reserved Brussels sprouts and mix with spatula until combined. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g mixed fresh herbs, leaves and tender stems, e.g. sage, parsley, thyme","500 g water","900 g Brussels sprouts, trimmed, halved","110 g shallots, quartered","220 g pancetta, diced (approx. 0.5 cm)","30 g unsalted butter","200 g cooked chestednuts, peeled","60 g sweet Marsala wine","1 Tbsp maple syrup","½ tsp fine sea salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r252618","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-DMeSSJK-74U\/XZWZXAtCtyI\/AAAAAAAAeLw\/S1_peN3_IZIIpoHoz2QG2SXe_lVoQQcvACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0__vmRFcOYnc9wH7nR.png","title":"Brussels Sprouts with Chestnuts and Pancetta","publishedAt":"2017-11-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"20 g","fat":"21 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"35 g","calories":"1674 kJ \/ 400 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["When buying Brussels sprouts, look for those that are bright and intense in colour. They should also be compact, round and smooth, tight and heavy for their size. The stem area should be clean and must be white. For large Brussels sprouts, cut into quarters.","Chestnuts are in season from autumn until mid-winter. Alternatively, precooked chestnuts can be purchased at speciality food shops or markets."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","6 portions"]}